<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-12-24T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-12-24T14:00:00-05:00" n="820" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d820">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/20135</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Carothers</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-12-24T12:00:00-07:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 24, 1916,
                                noon</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I have confirmation of capture of Torreon by Villa also that he is
                            maintaining order and affording protection to foreigners who
                            remained.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Carothers</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>